I'm going to the Hole.

36:31.969 --> 36:33.561
What? At 5:00?

36:33.637 --> 36:36.128
We're stopping at Laurie Kipper stein’s
house so I can wash my hair.

36:36.739 --> 36:37.763
Hi, Mr Gopnik.

36:38.141 --> 36:40.302
- You can't wash it here?
- Uncle Arthur's in the bathroom.

36:40.410 --> 36:41.968
I'll be out in a minute!

36:42.078 --> 36:43.136
- Are you ready?
- Huh?

36:43.246 --> 36:44.735
- We're meeting Sy at Embers.
- I am?

36:44.813 --> 36:47.145
Both of us.
I told you, Larry.

36:49.151 --> 36:50.379
Larry.

36:54.755 --> 36:55.813
How are you?

36:57.625 --> 36:58.648
Sy.

37:01.227 --> 37:02.251
Hello, Judith.

37:02.328 --> 37:03.317
Hello, Sy.

37:05.565 --> 37:08.795
Larry, I want to
thank you for coming.

37:09.101 --> 37:12.628
It's so important that we be
able to discuss these things.

37:12.738 --> 37:14.432
I'm happy to come
to Embers, Sy.

37:14.505 --> 37:16.996
But I'm thinking, really,
maybe it's best to leave

37:17.108 --> 37:18.439
these discussions
to the lawyers.

37:18.509 --> 37:21.341
Of course Legal matters,
you let the lawyers discuss.

37:21.445 --> 37:23.436
You don't mix
apples and oranges.

37:23.513 --> 37:24.946
I have begged you
to see the lawyer.

37:25.015 --> 37:26.277
I told you,
I'm going Monday.

37:26.349 --> 37:29.010
Monday is timely.
This is not...

37:29.118 --> 37:32.781
Please, Embers is not the forum
for legalities You're so right.

37:34.023 --> 37:37.514
No, Judith and I wanted
merely to discuss, uh,

37:38.359 --> 37:40.793
practicalities.
Living arrangements.

37:41.162 --> 37:44.961
After all, this is an issue
where no one is at odds.

37:45.032 --> 37:46.192
Living arrangements?

37:47.367 --> 37:50.597
I think we all agree
that the children

37:50.670 --> 37:53.764
not being contaminated
with the tension,

37:53.840 --> 37:54.966
the most important.

37:55.041 --> 37:57.032
We shouldn't put the kids
in the middle of this, Larry.

37:57.143 --> 37:58.166
The kids aren't...

37:58.276 --> 38:00.176
I'm saying "we. "
I'm not pointing fingers.

38:00.278 --> 38:02.974
No one is playing
the blame game, Larry.

38:03.048 --> 38:04.140
I didn't say
anyone was.

38:04.216 --> 38:06.183
Well, let's not play "He
Said, She Said," either.

38:06.317 --> 38:08.308
- I wasn't! I...
- All right. Look, look, look.

38:08.385 --> 38:12.151
Let's just take a step back and
we can diffuse the situation.

38:14.324 --> 38:17.851
You know, Larry,
sometimes I find that

38:17.961 --> 38:19.622
if I count to 10...

38:21.563 --> 38:22.621
One,

38:23.899 --> 38:24.888
two,

38:26.401 --> 38:27.459
three,

38:28.903 --> 38:30.131
four...

38:30.538 --> 38:32.403
Or silently.

38:39.846 --> 38:42.507
Really, to keep things
on an even keel

38:42.581 --> 38:44.481
leading up to
Danny's bar mitzvah...

38:44.550 --> 38:46.347
A child's
bar mitzvah, Larry.

38:46.418 --> 38:50.148
Sy and I think it's best if
you move out of the house.

38:51.489 --> 38:52.478
Move out?

38:52.590 --> 38:55.024
- Well, it makes eminent sense.
- Things can't continue as they...

38:55.093 --> 38:56.560
Move out?
Where would I go?

38:56.661 --> 38:59.720
Well, for instance, the
Jolly Roger is quite liveable.

38:59.830 --> 39:01.092
It's not expensive.

39:01.198 --> 39:03.758
The rooms are
eminently habitable.

39:03.867 --> 39:05.356
This would allow you
to visit the kids.

39:05.434 --> 39:07.527
There's convenience in its
favour They've got a pool.

39:07.603 --> 39:10.265
Wouldn't it make more sense
for you to move in with Sy?

39:12.240 --> 39:13.332
Larry.

39:13.742 --> 39:16.870
Larry, you...
You are jesting.

39:17.913 --> 39:20.710
I think, really,
the Jolly Roger

39:20.781 --> 39:23.841
is the appropriate
course of action.

39:29.289 --> 39:30.381
Listen here,

39:30.456 --> 39:32.117
you little fucker,
I want my money!

39:32.258 --> 39:33.520
Stop it!
I'm going to get it!

39:33.526 --> 39:34.549
Give it back!

39:34.626 --> 39:36.253
You owe me 20 bucks,
you little shit!

39:36.361 --> 39:38.295
- Don't worry about it!
- Give it, brat fucker!

39:38.430 --> 39:40.898
- I'm going to get it! I'm going to get it!
- Brat! Fucker!

39:40.966 --> 39:42.626
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

39:44.969 --> 39:47.028
- What was that?
- Nothing.

39:48.272 --> 39:49.761
How's the Torah
portion coming?

39:49.873 --> 39:52.239
Can you maybe
use the hi-fi?

39:52.309 --> 39:53.571
- What?
- Can I borrow this?

39:53.643 --> 39:57.544
I'm taking some stuff to,
you know, the Jolly Roger.

39:57.613 --> 39:58.739
- Dad!
- Sure, Dad.

39:58.814 --> 40:00.805
Dad! Chinese guy!

40:01.283 --> 40:02.375
Culture clash.

40:05.153 --> 40:06.279
Culture clash.

40:07.422 --> 40:10.391
With all respect, Mr. Park,
I don't think it's that.

40:10.458 --> 40:11.754
- Yes.
- No,

40:11.825 --> 40:15.420
it would be a culture clash if
it were the custom in your land

40:15.495 --> 40:16.928
to bribe people
for grades.

40:16.997 --> 40:18.123
Yes.

40:19.665 --> 40:21.826
So, you're saying
it is the custom?

40:21.934 --> 40:25.233
No, this is defamation.
Ground for lawsuit.

40:25.838 --> 40:26.929
Let me get this straight.

40:27.005 --> 40:29.599
You're threatening to sue
me for defaming your son?

40:29.674 --> 40:30.800
Yes.

40:31.443 --> 40:33.673
- But it would...
- Is this man bothering you?

40:34.912 --> 40:37.642
Is he bothering me? No.

40:39.617 --> 40:40.845
I, uh...

40:47.190 --> 40:48.521
See, look...

40:48.624 --> 40:50.285
If it were defamation,
there would have to be

40:50.359 --> 40:52.452
someone I was defaming him to, or I...

40:52.527 --> 40:54.586
All right,
let's keep it simple.

40:54.663 --> 40:58.098
I could pretend the money never
appeared That's not defaming anyone.

40:58.165 --> 41:00.531
Yes. And passing grade.

41:01.202 --> 41:02.829
- Passing grade?
- Yes.

41:03.837 --> 41:05.429
Or you'll sue me?

41:05.505 --> 41:06.631
For taking money.

41:06.706 --> 41:08.469
So he did leave the money?

41:08.541 --> 41:09.803
This is defamation!

41:11.043 --> 41:14.137
It doesn't make sense. Either
he left the money or he didn't.

41:14.213 --> 41:16.545
Please.
Accept the mystery.

41:19.951 --> 41:21.714
Give me that, fucker.

41:29.026 --> 41:30.288
He's very
good with numbers.

41:30.360 --> 41:33.726
I think his social skills
have held him back.

41:33.829 --> 41:35.820
Such a sweet man, though.

41:35.898 --> 41:37.195
Arthur has
a good heart.

41:38.300 --> 41:40.699
And he never complains,
unlike me.

41:41.736 --> 41:43.670
Sometimes I don't
give him enough credit.

41:43.738 --> 41:47.504
He tried to tell me about this
thing he's working on, this...

41:47.575 --> 41:49.405
The Meticulous.

41:50.244 --> 41:55.738
He says it's a probability
map of the universe.

41:56.749 --> 41:59.081
Does he go out
socially at all?

41:59.719 --> 42:03.176
He tries. He's been going to the
singles mixers at Hillel House.

42:05.424 --> 42:07.722
I should talk.
I'm not doing any better.

42:09.094 --> 42:10.355
How is Judith?

42:12.530 --> 42:15.192
Fine. She's fine.

42:17.068 --> 42:20.036
Sometimes these things
just aren't meant to be.

42:20.103 --> 42:24.005
And it can take a while before
you feel what was always there.

42:24.074 --> 42:26.439
- For better or worse.
- I never felt it!

42:27.443 --> 42:29.741
It was a bolt
from the blue.

42:29.845 --> 42:31.039
What does that mean?

42:31.113 --> 42:34.878
Everything that I thought was
one way turns out to be another.

42:35.917 --> 42:40.580
Then, it's an opportunity to
learn how things really are.

42:41.955 --> 42:43.354
I don't mean to sound glib.

42:45.759 --> 42:49.455
It's not always easy deciphering
what God is trying to tell you,

42:50.029 --> 42:53.192
but it's not something you have
to figure out all by yourself.

42:54.699 --> 42:55.961
We're Jews.

42:56.434 --> 43:00.370
We've got that well of tradition
to draw on, to help us understand.

43:01.039 --> 43:03.734
When we're puzzled,
we have all the stories

43:03.807 --> 43:07.538
that have been handed down from
people who had the same problems.

43:09.545 --> 43:11.570
Have you talked to
Rabbi Nachtner?

43:15.318 --> 43:16.285
Why not see him?

43:16.385 --> 43:18.045
What's the Rabbi
going to tell me?

43:18.453 --> 43:20.148
If I knew,
I'd be the Rabbi.

43:20.489 --> 43:24.220
The air out here is magnificent.

43:25.659 --> 43:29.823
I'm telling you, if someone
could bottle this air,

43:29.930 --> 43:31.726
they'd make
a million dollars.

43:48.513 --> 43:50.413
Hello, Larry.
Good to see you.

43:50.481 --> 43:51.846
Oh. Rabbi Scott.

43:53.184 --> 43:55.310
I thought I was going
to see Rabbi Nachtner.

43:55.418 --> 43:57.511
He was called away
on an etz monim.

43:57.621 --> 44:01.318
Ruth Bryn’s mother is in the
hospital and she isn't doing well.

44:01.423 --> 44:04.688
Rabbi Nachtner asked me to
cover for him. Come on in.

44:16.370 --> 44:19.771
And she wants a get.

44:24.777 --> 44:25.869
A what?

44:28.548 --> 44:30.345
- She wants a...
- Oh, a get.

44:30.449 --> 44:32.006
Uh-huh. Sure.

44:32.784 --> 44:35.480
I feel like the carpet's
been yanked out from under me.

44:35.554 --> 44:37.818
I don't know which end is up.

44:37.889 --> 44:39.685
I'm not even sure
how to react.

44:39.790 --> 44:41.121
I'm too confused.

44:41.559 --> 44:45.222
What reasons did she
give for the rupture?

44:45.329 --> 44:47.888
She didn't give reasons
Just that,

44:47.997 --> 44:50.227
you know, things
haven't been going well.

44:50.333 --> 44:51.391
And is that true?

44:52.068 --> 44:53.557
I guess.
I don't know.

44:53.669 --> 44:55.830
She's usually right
about these things.

44:55.904 --> 44:58.372
I was hoping that
Rabbi Nachtner could...

44:58.874 --> 45:00.898
That he would...
He would... Yes?

45:01.008 --> 45:03.238
Well, with the benefit
of his life experience.

45:04.011 --> 45:05.171
No offense.

45:05.246 --> 45:08.408
No, of course not I am the junior rabbi.

45:09.082 --> 45:12.848
And it's true, the point of
view of somebody who's older

45:12.919 --> 45:17.355
and perhaps had similar
problems might be more valid.

45:17.423 --> 45:20.483
And you should see the senior
rabbi as well, by all means.

45:20.559 --> 45:21.753
Or even Marshal,

45:22.261 --> 45:24.023
if you can get in.

45:24.095 --> 45:26.689
He's quite busy,
but maybe...

45:31.034 --> 45:32.558
Can I share
something with you?

45:32.936 --> 45:35.837
Because I, too, have had
the feeling of losing track

45:35.906 --> 45:38.703
of Hashem,
which is the problem here.

45:39.242 --> 45:42.040
I, too, have forgotten
how to see him in the world,

45:42.111 --> 45:44.170
and when that happens,
you think,

45:44.247 --> 45:48.239
"Well, if I can't see him,
he isn't there. He's gone. "

45:48.516 --> 45:50.108
But that's not the case.

45:50.619 --> 45:53.610
You just need to
remember how to see him.

45:53.721 --> 45:56.019
Am I right? I mean...

45:57.124 --> 45:59.115
The parking lot here.

46:02.128 --> 46:03.561
Not much to see.

46:04.197 --> 46:06.893
But if you imagine
yourself a visitor,

46:07.733 --> 46:11.635
somebody who isn't familiar
with these autos and such,

46:11.737 --> 46:14.297
somebody still with
the capacity for wonder.

46:14.406 --> 46:17.568
Someone with
a fresh perspective.

46:18.142 --> 46:19.439
That's what it is, Larry.

46:19.543 --> 46:21.568
Because with
the right perspective,

46:21.646 --> 46:25.103
you can see Hashem, you
know, reaching into the world.

46:25.215 --> 46:27.945
He is in the world,
not just in shul.

46:28.652 --> 46:33.554
It sounds to me like you're looking
at the world, looking at your wife,

46:33.622 --> 46:35.556
through tired eyes.

46:36.225 --> 46:39.819
It sounds like she's
become a sort of thing...

46:40.561 --> 46:42.085
A problem.

46:42.630 --> 46:43.756
A thing.

46:43.831 --> 46:45.957
She is seeing Sy Able man.

46:50.771 --> 46:52.601
- Oh.
- They're planning...

46:52.672 --> 46:54.139
That's why
they want the get.

46:54.240 --> 46:56.470
Oh I'm sorry.

46:56.575 --> 46:58.099
It was his idea.

46:58.177 --> 47:03.614
Well, they do need a get
to remarry in the faith.

47:04.849 --> 47:07.840
But... This is life.

47:08.852 --> 47:12.686
You have to see these things
as expressions of God's will.

47:12.790 --> 47:14.689
You don't have to
like it, of course.

47:15.124 --> 47:17.456
The boss isn't always right,
but he's always the boss.

47:17.527 --> 47:19.324
That's right!

47:19.929 --> 47:21.157
Things aren't so bad.

47:21.264 --> 47:23.527
Look at
the parking lot, Larry.

47:25.200 --> 47:27.430
Just look at
that parking lot.

47:43.483 --> 47:44.710
Are we eating already?

47:44.817 --> 47:46.216
Sarah's going out.

47:46.885 --> 47:48.182
Ow! Cut it out!

47:48.287 --> 47:49.515
What's going on?

47:55.827 --> 47:56.816
Isn't Dad eating?

47:56.894 --> 47:58.225
He's at the Jolly Roger.

47:59.296 --> 48:00.524
Oh, yeah.

48:05.902 --> 48:06.993
How are you, Larry?

48:07.069 --> 48:09.560
Jesus, I am so sorry

48:09.705 --> 48:12.196
- to be seeing you under these
circumstances. - Oh, well...

48:12.308 --> 48:14.867
I always thought you
and Judy were rock solid.

48:14.976 --> 48:18.207
This is so terrible, Larry.
This is devastating.

48:18.313 --> 48:19.678
Well, you know,
the way I look at it,

48:19.748 --> 48:23.308
it's an opportunity for me to
really sit down and figure things out

48:23.384 --> 48:27.650
and look at the world afresh
instead of just, you know,

48:27.721 --> 48:31.656
settling for the routine, tired
old way of looking at things.

48:33.426 --> 48:34.552
Really?

48:35.861 --> 48:37.328
I don't know,
maybe not.

48:38.997 --> 48:42.330
Well, legally,
I have to warn you,

48:42.401 --> 48:44.868
it's never easy
for the husband.

48:44.935 --> 48:47.768
Unless, of course,
there's some question

48:47.872 --> 48:52.103
of the wife having violated
the marriage contract?

48:52.208 --> 48:54.233
Oh, no, no
Nothing like that.

48:54.344 --> 48:56.904
Although she is planning to
marry Sy Able man, but they...

48:57.013 --> 48:58.377
Sy Able man!

48:59.448 --> 49:02.542
- Yes. But they...
- Esther is barely cold!

49:03.352 --> 49:04.683
She passed
three years ago.

49:04.753 --> 49:08.950
Well... Still, this changes
the complexion, Larry.

49:09.424 --> 49:10.789
Sy Able man.

49:10.892 --> 49:13.689
Not in the sense that... T
here hasn't been hanky-panky.

49:13.760 --> 49:14.852
To my knowledge.

49:14.961 --> 49:18.226
- Oh? - No I'm fairly
certain this is not an issue.

49:18.298 --> 49:21.460
And in fact,
Judith wants a get.

49:24.036 --> 49:25.128
A what?

49:26.305 --> 49:27.794
A ritual divorce.

49:27.906 --> 49:30.033
- Oh.
- So that they can remarry in the faith.

49:30.108 --> 49:32.372
Uh-huh.
Yeah, sure, uh...

49:32.444 --> 49:34.469
Well, not really
a legal issue.

49:36.380 --> 49:37.642
Okay, um...

49:38.715 --> 49:40.580
Good. Good.

49:41.385 --> 49:43.079
Well...

49:43.152 --> 49:46.588
On the other thing, the
neighbour’s property line,

49:46.656 --> 49:49.284
I've asked Solomon
Schultz to take a look.

49:49.392 --> 49:52.758
There's very little to do with
real estate that'll get by Sol.

49:52.828 --> 49:54.591
Okay Good
How do you...

49:54.663 --> 49:56.153
I guess
I'm a little worried.

49:56.264 --> 49:58.424
How do you...
I have money pressures...

49:58.499 --> 50:00.592
Our fee structure?
We bill by the hour.

50:00.668 --> 50:03.933
Dave Sieglestein and
Solomon Schultz bill at 110.

50:04.004 --> 50:06.836
The associates, me,
for instance, bill at...

50:06.940 --> 50:09.408
Call for Mr Gopnik
Danny at home.

50:09.476 --> 50:11.501
You can take it here.

50:13.679 --> 50:14.805
SECRETARY:

50:16.748 --> 50:17.737
Danny?

50:17.816 --> 50:19.443
- Hey, Dad.
- Are you all right?

50:19.518 --> 50:20.506
Are you all...

50:20.618 --> 50:21.983
F Troop is fuzzy.

50:23.855 --> 50:25.117
What?

50:25.189 --> 50:26.952
F Troop is still fuzzy.

50:29.860 --> 50:31.691
- Dad?
- Is everything okay?

51:58.436 --> 51:59.425
Clive?

52:02.707 --> 52:03.695
Clive!

52:05.576 --> 52:08.374
You little bastard! You
going to send your mother next?

52:10.447 --> 52:12.277
Little bastard!
I want to see you!

52:21.122 --> 52:22.111
Hold on.

52:22.524 --> 52:24.583
Professor Gopnik,
it's Dick Dutton again.

52:25.393 --> 52:26.450
Dick Dutton.

52:28.529 --> 52:29.553
Hello?

52:29.630 --> 52:31.188
Hello, Mr Gopnik?

52:31.265 --> 52:33.960
This is Dick Dutton from
the Columbia Record Club.

52:34.067 --> 52:37.093
I'm calling because
it's now four months,

52:37.203 --> 52:39.569
and we have yet to
receive your first payment.

52:42.074 --> 52:43.564
There's some mistake.

52:43.642 --> 52:45.974
I'm not a member
of the Columbian Record Club.

52:46.078 --> 52:49.774
Sir, you are Lawrence Gopnik
of 8419 Fern Hill Road?

52:49.880 --> 52:51.575
No, I live
at the Jolly Roger.

52:51.649 --> 52:52.741
Excuse me?

52:53.417 --> 52:54.714
No, I...

52:55.619 --> 52:57.780
Well, yes, okay.

52:57.887 --> 52:59.787
- Yes, you are Lawrence Gopnik?
- Okay.

53:00.490 --> 53:01.548
"Okay" means...

53:01.625 --> 53:03.888
Okay, yes,
Lawrence Gopnik, yes.

53:03.959 --> 53:06.928
Okay, well, you received
your 12 introductory albums,

53:06.996 --> 53:10.556
and you've been receiving the monthly
main selection for four months now...

53:10.632 --> 53:12.259
The monthly main selection?
Is that a record?

53:12.333 --> 53:14.096
I didn't ask
for any records.

53:14.168 --> 53:17.331
To receive the monthly main
selection, you do nothing. You...

53:18.190 --> 53:19.748
That's right.
I haven't done anything.

53:19.859 --> 53:22.521
Yes, that's why you received
the monthly main selection.

53:22.661 --> 53:27.359
- But...
- The last one was Santana Abraxas. You...

53:27.432 --> 53:30.890
I didn't ask
for Santana Abraxas.

53:31.002 --> 53:33.094
You request
the main selection

53:33.203 --> 53:35.694
at the retail price
by doing nothing.

53:35.773 --> 53:37.707
It's automatically
mailed to you,

53:37.775 --> 53:39.265
plus shipping
and handling.

53:39.410 --> 53:42.207
- You're about to receive...
- I can't afford a new record every month!

53:42.278 --> 53:43.677
I haven't asked...

53:43.746 --> 53:46.715
You're about to get
Cosmo's Factory, sir.

53:46.783 --> 53:48.374
The June
main selection.

53:48.450 --> 53:50.918
Look, look,
something is very wrong!

53:51.019 --> 53:53.214
I don't want
Santana Abraxas.

53:53.288 --> 53:55.448
I've just been
in a terrible auto accident.

53:59.627 --> 54:00.787
I'm sorry, sir.

54:02.695 --> 54:06.062
Well, thank you.
But I...

54:06.966 --> 54:07.955
Are you okay?

54:10.102 --> 54:13.071
Yes, yes.
No one was hurt.

54:14.306 --> 54:16.797
Okay. Good.

54:18.109 --> 54:22.239
Well, you had 14 days to
listen to Santana Abraxas.

54:22.313 --> 54:23.371
- Sir?
- Look...

54:23.448 --> 54:26.143
I didn't ask for Santana Abraxas,

54:26.249 --> 54:29.741
I didn't listen
to Santana Abraxas,

54:29.820 --> 54:31.754
